# Design tokens

All UI tokens are defined in `client/src/global.css` using OKLCH color space. Always reference semantic tokens — never use raw Tailwind palette colors for UI meaning.

## Colors

Use **only** semantic token classes. These map to CSS variables that auto-switch for dark mode.

| Purpose | Use | Never use |
|---------|-----|-----------|
| Success feedback | `text-success`, `bg-success-muted`, `border-success/20` | `text-green-600`, `bg-green-50` |
| Error / destructive | `text-destructive`, `bg-destructive/10`, `border-destructive/20` | `text-red-600`, `bg-red-50`, `border-red-200` |
| Warning | `text-warning`, `bg-warning-muted`, `border-warning/20` | `text-amber-600`, `text-orange-500` |
| Info | `text-info`, `bg-info-muted`, `border-info/20` | `text-blue-600`, `bg-blue-50` |
| Muted/secondary text | `text-muted-foreground` | `text-gray-500`, `text-black/50` |
| Backgrounds | `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `bg-muted` | `bg-white`, `bg-gray-100` |
| Full-page gradients | `bg-background` only | `bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-100` |

Exception: Landing page hero/features use `black`/`white` with opacity for editorial contrast. Dashboard and app chrome must use tokens.

## Border radius

Base: `--radius: 0.625rem`. Scale defined in `@theme inline`.

| Element | Class | Usage |
|---------|-------|-------|
| Buttons, inputs | `rounded-md` | Standard interactive elements |
| Cards, panels, sections | `rounded-lg` | Content containers |
| Feature cards (landing) | `rounded-2xl` | Large editorial cards |
| Avatars, pills, badges | `rounded-full` | Circular/pill elements |

## Borders

| Strength | Class | When |
|----------|-------|------|
| Strong divider | `border-border` | Header/sidebar dividers, `<hr>` |
| Card/panel | `border-border/40` | Section cards in dashboard |
| Subtle container | `border-border/50` | Alerts, inner panels |
| Status accent | `border-{status}/20` | Alert left bars, inline errors |

Width is always 1px (default `border`). Only use `border-2` for focus rings or active states.

## Spacing

Standardized padding/gap values:

| Context | Padding | Gap |
|---------|---------|-----|
| Page content area | `px-8 py-4` | — |
| Section card | `p-6` | `space-y-4` |
| Compact block (alert) | `px-4 py-3` | `gap-3` |
| Card list items | `p-3` | `gap-2` |
| Feature sections (landing) | `p-8 md:p-10` | `gap-6` |

Prefer these standard values. Avoid one-off spacing like `p-7`, `gap-2.5`, `px-5` unless for precise alignment.
